Revision history for browser

0.14 2026-04-24
 - reject relative PATH hits such as `bin/chrome` when selecting a browser binary for Playwright
 - validate configured and discovered browser binaries with a quiet launchability check before passing them as `executablePath`
 - add fallback candidate handling for common macOS app bundle browser locations without trusting broken wrappers

0.13 2026-04-24
 - add `dashboard browser.png` to capture a rendered page screenshot
 - support `--file` with automatic `.png` suffix normalization when the caller omitted it
 - default screenshot output to a random `/tmp/browser-*.png` path and print the saved file path after capture

0.12 2026-04-22
 - repair Node runtime self-healing so stale merged module trees do not leave `uuid` in an ESM-broken state for `playwright_server`
 - align runtime installation with DD's staged `npx` package.json install pattern and clear affected module directories before copying fresh installs into `$HOME/node_modules`
 - auto-detect a usable Chromium or Chrome binary from `PATH` when `CHROMIUM_BIN` is not set
 - verify the runtime fix through Docker, direct host CLI execution, and the latest DD source checkout

0.11 2026-04-22
 - add `--wait-until` so callers can choose `networkidle`, `load`, or `domcontentloaded`
 - remove unproven documentation examples and keep only verified examples in the README
 - update public-site examples so Amazon uses `--wait-until load` where appropriate

0.10 2026-04-22
 - add 20 Amazon-focused examples covering search, account, cart, and product-page patterns
 - add 20 X-focused examples covering logged-out shell inspection, login, post viewing, and multi-page flows
 - record the live DOM verification limitation for Amazon and the live logged-out shell alignment for X

0.09 2026-04-22
 - expand the README with explicit JavaScript versus Perl controller guidance
 - document when `--jquery` is useful and how to mix Perl control with page-side JavaScript
 - add a large example library covering one-page tasks, multi-page flows, normal cases, and edge cases

0.08 2026-04-22
 - change ask-mode initial navigation to use `load` instead of `networkidle`
 - disable the initial ask-mode timeout by default so slow login pages stay open for manual work
 - keep `--timeout-ms` as an explicit override for bounded waits

0.07 2026-04-22
 - add `--playwright`, `--agent`, and `--flow` as controller-mode aliases for full Perl-side Playwright flows
 - make `--ask` compatible with controller-mode flows so manual login or CAPTCHA work can continue into scripted navigation
 - update tests and docs for multi-page browser journeys from one starting URL

0.06 2026-04-22
 - add `--jquery` to inject the local jQuery runtime into the page before script evaluation
 - document that Playwright itself does not provide jQuery unless the page already loaded it
 - update tests and docs for jQuery-enabled scripts

0.05 2026-04-22
 - add `--ask` and `--askme` to browser.get for visible interactive takeover
 - wait for terminal confirmation before capturing the final page payload after captcha or login work
 - update tests and docs for interactive ask-mode

0.04 2026-04-22
 - add `content_type`, `body_text`, and `is_captcha` to browser responses
 - detect obvious CAPTCHA or bot-check pages in browser.get and browser.post payloads
 - update tests and docs for the richer response payload

0.03 2026-04-22
 - make browser.get return the rendered HTML body alongside URL, status, and title metadata
 - update tests and docs to match the browser.get payload contract

0.02 2026-04-21
 - add package.json for DD-managed Node dependency installation
 - align browser runtime bootstrap with DD package.json install behavior under $HOME
 - update tests and docs for the package.json dependency gate

0.01 2026-04-21
 - bootstrap the browser skill with Playwright-backed GET and POST CLI commands
 - add dependency files for nodejs and the Playwright Perl module
 - add Docker-tested coverage, documentation, and ticket records
